This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with optical flow algorithms and their performance on crowd behavior analysis. It may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it involves the generation of video sequences with ground-truth optical flow. Additionally, machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories may be relevant as the paper evaluates different optical flow algorithms and provides new insights into crowd analysis. Finally, the paper may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category as it mentions real-world surveillance scenarios.
